Kirinyaga Governor Anne Waiguru and Coast leaders arrived for the BBI rally at Mama Ngina Waterfront Park on Saturday. A large crowd gathered for the event, with matatus offering free transport to the venue. Governor Hassan Joho will lead the rally. Joho and his counterparts Dhado Godana of Tana River, Amason Kingi of Kilifi and Granton Samboja of Taita Taveta county cautioned against any malicious motive during the meeting. Kwale Woman Representative Zuleikha Hassan Juma is among Coast politicians to attend. Also expected are DP William Ruto allies. They include Elgeyo Marakwet Senator Kipchumba Murkomen, Susan Kihika (Nakuru senator), Moses Kuria (Gatundu South MP), Alice Wahome (Kandara MP) and Mohamed Ali (Nyali MP). On Tuesday, Murkomen announced they would attend future meetings. "After consultations as leaders... we will participate and, where necessary, take charge of these public rallies beginning with Mombasa this weekend," he said. Murkomen said they will support existing efforts and complement the already scheduled rallies.